    "problemStatement": "Consider a bijective function $ƒ$\n$$\nf: {1, 2, 3, \\dots, n} \\rightarrow {1, 2, 3, \\dots, n}\n$$\n\n\n\nWe have $M$  different color. We have to associate a color to every $x \\in {1, 2, 3, ... n}$ with one of the color such that $x$ and$ƒ(ƒ(x))$ has same  color .\n\n\nLet **G** be an array, where **G[x] = pair(ƒ[x], color[x])**. \n\nFind the number of distinct arrays **G** modulo 1000000007.",
